\par \pard\plain \s2\sa43\keep \f2\fs20\cf6 ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
\par \pard\plain \s6\li360\sa31 \f2\fs16 IdleWild is a screen-saver Windows application.  Its purpose is to protect your screen.
\par 
\par If you are away from your computer for a period of time and your monitor remains on, there is extra wear on your screen.  It does not need to be active.  IdleWild checks to see how long you have been "idle";  that is, not typing or mov
ing the mouse.  After a predetermined length of time, it blanks the screen, replacing it with an animated graphic of your choice.  To return to your original screen, simply move the mouse, click either of the mouse buttons, or press any key.
\par 
\par When IdleWild blanks your screen, it does not affect the applications you have running.  It simply adds a patterned image "on top" of them.  You can set a timer so that this image displays after a predetermined 
amount of "idle" time and vanishes instantly once you become "active" again.
\par 
\par When IdleWild is runni
ng, there are two special control locations on your screen.  If you position the pointer in the upper-right corner, IdleWild blanks the screen instantly.  If you position the pointer in the lower-left corner, screen blanking is temporarily inactive.

\par 
\par \pard\plain \s17\li360\sb60\sa187 \f2\fs16 {\cf6 Note:}  If the active window is running a DOS application or a Microsoft tutorial, screen blanking is disabled, because IdleWild is unable to keep track of the "idle" time in a DOS application or tutorial.

