\par 
\par \pard\plain \s13\sa86 \b\f2\fs16\cf2 To Begin Screen Blanking:
\par \pard\plain \s17\li360\sb60\sa187 \f2\fs16 \{bmc blkarow.bmp\}\tab Screen blanking is automatically active as soon as you run IdleWild.
\par {\cf6 Note:}  IdleWild must be running in order for the screen to blank.  It can be minimized, but it must be active.
\par \pard\plain \s13\sa86 \b\f2\fs16\cf2 To End Screen Blanking:
\par \pard\plain \s17\li360\sb60\sa187 \f2\fs16 \{bmc blkarow.bmp\}\tab From the Options menu, choose Exit.
\par {\cf6 Note:}  Choosing Close from the System menu also ends screen blanking.
\par \pard\plain \s13\sa86 \b\f2\fs16\cf2 To Set the Delay Before Blanking:
\par \pard\plain \s14\fi-360\li720\sa43\tx720 \f2\fs16 1\tab From the Options menu, choose Set Delay.
\par \pard\plain \s17\li360\sb60\sa187 \f2\fs16 2\tab Type the number of minutes in the dialog box, and then choose OK.
\par \pard\plain \s13\sa86 \b\f2\fs16\cf2 To Choose a Screen Blanker:
\par \pard\plain \s17\li360\sb60\sa187 \f2\fs16 \{bmc blkarow.bmp\}\tab Click the left mouse button on the name of the pattern you want.
\par \pard\plain \s13\sa86 \b\f2\fs16\cf2 To Blank the Screen Immediately:
\par \pard\plain \s17\li360\sb60\sa187 \f2\fs16 \{bmc blkarow.bmp\}\tab From the Options menu, choose Blank Now.
\par \{bmc blkarow.bmp\}\tab Double-click the name of any pattern.
\par \{bmc blkarow.bmp\}\tab Position the pointer in the upper-right corner of the screen.
