\par 
\par \pard\plain \s13\sa86 \b\f2\fs16\cf2 Set Delay
\par \pard\plain \s21\li360\sa180\tx1080 \f2\fs16 Sets the delay time. If the delay time is four minutes and you are idle for four minutes, the screen goes blank.
\par \pard\plain \s13\sa86 \b\f2\fs16\cf2 Blank Pointer
\par \pard\plain \s21\li360\sa180\tx1080 \f2\fs16 Stops displaying the mouse pointer, or insertion point, if it remains motionless for longer than ten seconds.  A check mark next to the command indicates it is active.
\par \pard\plain \s13\sa86 \b\f2\fs16\cf2 Autoload
\par \pard\plain \s21\li360\sa180\tx1080 \f2\fs16 Loads IdleWild automatically when you run Windows.  A check mark next to the command indicates it is active.
\par \pard\plain \s13\sa86 \b\f2\fs16\cf2 Blank Now
\par \pard\plain \s21\li360\sa180\tx1080 \f2\fs16 Blanks the screen immediately.
\par \pard\plain \s17\li360\sb60\sa187 \f2\fs16 {\cf6 Note:}  You can also blank the screen immediately by double-clicking the name of a pattern in the list box.
\par \pard\plain \s13\sa86 \b\f2\fs16\cf2 Exit
\par \pard\plain \s21\li360\sa180\tx1080 \f2\fs16 Stops IdleWild from blanking your screen.
